### D. New Project Bootstrap Checklist

Every new Khwarizmi project must run these steps before any UI generation:

```bash
# 1. Install Syncfusion packages
npm install @syncfusion/ej2-react-grids @syncfusion/ej2-react-inputs \
  @syncfusion/ej2-react-navigations @syncfusion/ej2-react-notifications \
  @syncfusion/ej2-react-buttons @syncfusion/ej2-react-dropdowns \
  @syncfusion/ej2-react-charts @syncfusion/ej2-react-calendars \
  @syncfusion/ej2-react-layouts @syncfusion/ej2-react-kanban \
  @syncfusion/ej2-react-schedule

# 2. Register Syncfusion license
SyncfusionLicense.registerLicense('YOUR_LICENSE_KEY');
```

```tsx
// 3. App root setup — RTL + Arabic locale
import { enableRtl, L10n, setCulture } from '@syncfusion/ej2-base';
import arLocale from './locales/ar.json';

enableRtl(true);
setCulture('ar');
L10n.load({ ar: arLocale });
```

```css
/* 4. Global CSS — Material-3 theme */
@import '@syncfusion/ej2/material3.css';
/* Dark mode: add .e-dark-mode to <html> or <body> */
```

```tsx
// 5. Root element
<html dir="rtl" lang="ar">
  <body className="e-khwarizmi"> {/* or e-dark-mode for dark */}
```

### E. Rules
- Load files 1–3 as Always Apply in every session.
- Load domain rules based on the UI element being generated.
- Higher priority files win all conflicts.
- Never generate UI without loading the global system and token rules at minimum.
- Do not skip vision.rules.md — it governs all AI behavior.
- All component generation must reference `components.rules.md` for the Syncfusion mapping table.
